text:
First hour walkthrough:
- Building Shaders;
- Loading Screen;
- Oh non, crash crash!
- Building Shaders;
- Loading Screen;
- Joel gone deaf
- Textures go pop pop Kingdom Come riding Al-Buraq with game on HDD inspired
- VRAM inflation

As of now, the game is poorly optimised and has bothersome bugs, (as what it seems to be the case for a lot of newly released games nowadays) the listening mode doesn't work, loading screens taking forever on SSD setups, stutters everywhere, the goddamn textures taking their sweet time to load even when you are right by the object's side and fiercely gazing at it. 
   I swear, I saw a construction car suddenly turning from a smudged black unloaded texture to a sharp bright yellow texture when I took cover on it. It feels like I' playing Kingdom Come Deliverance in an HDD. Never had this texture load problem with my SSD before, in any game.

The game looks incredible, but unfortunately It is incredibly bad optimized. As soon as I open the game, It takes about five to ten minutes for it to crash. If I make any faster moves with my mouse, the game crashes. I couldn't even get passed the first part of the game with Sarah, because the crashes have been stopping me from making it. The game is also not stable, even at a high FPS average (80-85), It feels a bit laggy and not really smooth. Maybe in a further patch the game can be enjoyed, as it should've been in Its release.

My PC: GIGABYTE RTX 3070 8 GB Eagle OC;
             Ryzen 5 5600x;
             32 GB RAM @ 3600 MHz;
             I'm using HD, not SSD.

I wish there was a mixed option; 
runs poorly 
slow story but good
